description.narrative:
The project "Promotion of Women face Resilience to Climate Change Effects and Access Rights to Production Resources"aims to contribute to the strengthening of women's resilience to the effects of climate change and to improve their knowledge concerning their rights of access to production resources. It will&nbsp;be implemented by the NGO AMAPROS for a period of 05 years from January 2016 to December 2020.&nbsp; It will&nbsp; contribute to strengthening women's resilience to the effects of climate change and to improve their knowledge on their rights of access to production resources&nbsp;in the regions of Segou and Koulikoro.&nbsp;This project is a coherent set of initiatives working to implement the following change: women 16-50 years have strengthened their resilience to the effects of climate change and assert their rights of access to productive resources in areas of intervention.This project is the result of the project "Support for the Fight against Labour and Trafficking of Children through Education in Agro-Industry sylvopastoral in circles Niono and Koulikoro" implemented by AMAPROS with the support of Diakonia from&nbsp; 2012 to 2015. Due to the great achievements of this previous period which allowed children to access to education and created &nbsp;income generation activities for women, this current project will consolidate the&nbsp;change&nbsp;occured specially to strenghen women capacities in reduction of the effects of climate change.&nbsp;
